It's assumed they asked for a name, otherwise they'd have no leads at all on who it (was) at all. (They can't exactly use DNA tests, or take photos, etc.). It's possible that anybody this person kept in touch with before abduction has either long forgotten or since died. Not to mention, laying on a workbench for ## years is bound to screw with somebody's memory.

Besides, I didn't think that info was really needed.  But if more people say it would be better if added then I might as well.







